<subSubSection id="CA3506C8B876DCDFE10DEA8AA5E905D9" pageId="11" pageNumber="114" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="0FCA7ECE92517A3066B0B0BFC4DED32D" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="14C37A7D187FA428A07454B2F5C321D1" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName id="4A6F51B2F3BB9EFE5DAEEBECBAAC9952" class="Insecta" family="Acroceridae" genus="Eulonchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eulonchus marginatus" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">Eulonchus marginatus</taxonomicName>
has been recorded visiting the flowers of 10 different plant families and 14 different species (Table 2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
