</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2142CD97A12BEBCEE0E9864B04832823" pageId="11" pageNumber="114" type="comments">
<paragraph id="A68664A7D2F381DB249766B085690840" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B7EF83C201BBB6AEF34140AC02D495D" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName id="1636B5AD6CAB072CC33DD8727C19BAD9" class="Insecta" family="Acroceridae" genus="Eulonchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eulonchus marginatus" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">Eulonchus marginatus</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="C3BC977798E0E4876589C2CC6386BB58" class="Insecta" family="Acroceridae" genus="Eulonchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eulonchus tristis" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">Eulonchus tristis</taxonomicName>
, sharing features such as extensive white thoracic pile and dark colouration on the legs. 
<taxonomicName id="E56E7CE9A06BA7710DE8993025B78885" class="Insecta" family="Acroceridae" genus="Eulonchus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eulonchus marginatus" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">Eulonchus marginatus</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from other species in the genus by the leg colour, trifurcate ocellar tubercle and dark margin of the calypter. This species displays considerable variation in body colour, ranging from metallic green, blue to purple.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
